		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">Gordon on the official EQ board</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=126265" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top">
		    <p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    <Blockquote>
<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/037560.html">Expansion spells, where are they?</a><P>

Aside from the ones that you can buy from Kunark vendors, where are these new spells? I heard Sky, but I know a lot of people that were there over the weekend, and they saw ZERO spells drop. Has anyone found them? I heard about a L60 mage pet spell dropping in Skyfire, but that is it. Could it be that Verant hasnt added them yet? This is ridiculous.<P>

<B>50+ spells are either obtained via merchants, quests, or loot drops. They are out there, but you'll probably want to make your way to an area that is a little more ripe with magic.<P> 

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/037640.html">Can Enchanters have Illusion:Specter ?</a><P>

<B>Though we certainly appreciate everyone's desire to look "cool", we don't want to open this model up to player characters.<P> 

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/037656.html">Mana regen Nerf? - Abashi Question</a><P>

Not to sound like I am complaining, but did the mana-regeneration formula somehow get lowered ? I only say this .. I spent 12 hours online on Saturday .. my mana used to regen to three bubbles in around 4 minutes and to full in 7-7.5 ( with a wisdom of 181 ) .. on saturday however it seemed that I regained my mana at a lowered pace .. getting 3 bubbles in 8 minutes and back to full in about 11 or 12 .. was the formula adjusted or am I just hallucinating from spending to much time in Kunark?<P>

<B>There has been no intentional change, however due to the number of people reporting it I'm not ready to dismiss it just yet. However, I highly suspect that the observations are due to a number of things, not related to the actual rate. For instance:<P>

1. Perception: Mana above level 50 continues to increase at a rate much like it was before, however the mana regen rate does not increase on the same curve, giving the perception that it takes longer to med, even though you are still getting the same amount of mana back per tick. This is something that people also notice and claim as they level up or gain +INT/WIS/MANA items. They increase the amount of mana that they have without increasing the regen rate in a linear manner.<P> 

2. Watched Pot: The addition of Kunark has caused people to spread out more. The net result of this is that the ratio of people to targets has improved. Where a group used to be at full mana the next time it was their "turn" to kill a particular spawn, they are now staring at their mana bars while a surplus of critters walk by that they could be killing.<P> 

3. Placebo Effect: The "Placebo effect" also causes the "Watched Pot". Someone, perhaps due to one of the reasons mentioned above, perceives that the mana regen rate has changed, and comments on it. This causes other people to become sensitive to the issue, causing them to pay close attention to their mana bars, giving the impression that it is taking longer to regen.<P>

4. Of course there is always the good old fashioned "bug", which shouldn't take too long for us to figure out as soon as I can corner the programmers  I'm looking into it this afternoon.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/037687.html">Why do snakes kick?</a><P>

This makes no sense to me.<P>

<B>The skills that NPCs have are based on level and class, not on the model that they use. For instance, that puma that you are fighting might really be monk. I suppose that it might have been nice if we had a way to suppress the use of certain skills based upon body type.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/037731.html">Loot tables changed - Who gets hurt... Those that had delayed shipments</a><P>

They should have stayed the same so everyone had the same opportunity... What about the people still waiting for thier CD's?<P>

<B>If "fairness" is the main concern here, there's really no way to make these changes "fair". Certainly we could have waited until everyone (within reason) received their CD's, but the same subject of fairness would come up for those who have had their CDs and just now decided to make the trip to Kunark.<P>

Yes, the 10s of thousands of people entering Kunark did bring a few loot issues to light. There were cases where loot was dropping in the wrong place, and it has in most cases been moved to a more appropriate location. We even had a few dragon/god items dropping on level 40 creatures (though at very small percentages), and the people who were there first certainly lucked out. Unfortunately at some time we have to fix these errors, and making it fair in everyone's eyes probably isn't possible.<P> 

Please, lets not look at this as people who got there later getting hurt, but perhaps as people who got there sooner getting lucky.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/037739.html">Tishan's Relocation = Mass Suicide</a><P>

Well, I can't see the usefullness of group evac'ing a party to the middle of Skyfire mountains where numerous aggro 45+ MOBS are ready to eat your already HP and Mana depleted group for lunch. Gordon, please help us wizards see the point of this spell and why I wasted 19pp to only to get 6 honest people killed?<P>

<B>Sounds like you might have gotten a bit unlucky with that cast. We'll check the destination and look to see whether we can move it someplace a little safer, but as a general rule I'd consider that spell a last-ditch effort to save the group without leaving the zone.<P> 

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/037784.html">Class Envy Posts.</a><P>

<B>I just got done taking a look at the first page of this forum. As I'm sure many know, each page holds 40 threads. Of the 40 threads at the time that I'm writing this:<P>

13 are complaining about rogues<BR>
2 about rangers<BR>
2 about paladins<BR>
1 about wizards<BR>
1 about magicians<BR>
1 about druids<BR>
1 about enchanters<BR>
1 about necros<P>

That's over half of the posts on the first page that basically consist of "My class isn't balanced, isn't powerful enough, isn't desired in groups, can't do something some other class can." or something along those lines. The other 18 posts are perhaps issues that we'd like to answer, but people constantly bumping the class-envy posts keeps pushing them down. That isn't fair to the people who have issues that we can and are willing to address or do something about.<P> 

I'm very sorry if we haven't been able to give everyone the answer that they are looking for in regards to their class, but being as clear as possible, notwithstanding current planned and announced enhancements, we consider all classes to be essentially well-balanced at this time. This means that we feel that there is a compelling reason to play each class beyond the desire to roleplay. It does not mean that every class is equivalent in offensive power, desirability to a group, or has some unique special skill or ability, just that there are tangible reasons someone might choose to play your class.<P>

I don't wish to get involved in the unending recursive arguments that surround class-envy posts any longer (e.g. Explain how we are balanced, what is the compelling reason to play us, etc). This is all meant to be part of the discovery process in the game. Part of the process where everyone finds out what character class suits them. We can’t tell you what you should like about your class, and if there is no other way to convince to you like your class other than to start handing out enhancements, then we may be at an impasse.<P>

If you wish to keep discussing these issues on our boards, it’s perfectly fine. We’ll read them and we may respond to some issues raised from time to time providing that the content is respectful and the answer would be of benefit to players as a whole, but we won’t feel compelled to answer class-envy posts regardless how many people comment in them. We’ll close the threads when they hit between 300-400 posts, and if the number of threads reach spam proportions (like the 13 rogue posts on the first page), we’ll start closing them before that.<P> 

It is not at all our intention to suppress anyone’s ability to discuss these issues, but we want to be sure that people with issues that we can address, and that we’d like to address, have priority on the boards.<P> 

Thank you for understanding, and I do intend to follow up on this thread today if content allows.<P>

-Gordon</B>
</blockquote>
		    </font></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
